Others: The Utah Jazz were shorthanded with five rotation players missing in the game.
The Jazz got key contributions from their rookies and second unit to keep pace with Phoenix.
The Suns' efficient offense and Utah's cold 3-point shooting (9-of-42, 21.4 percent) proved to be too much to overcome.
Utah's defense locked in during the second half, but the Suns offense found its rhythm and held a nine-point lead going into the fourth quarter.
Kyle Filipowski and Cody Williams impressed with their performances off the bench for the Jazz.
Svi Mykhailiuk and Drew Eubanks combined for two pick-and-roll connections as Utah's second unit continued to produce.
Grayson Allen left his mark on the game with three 3-pointers as the Suns once again pushed their lead to double digits.
The Jazz kept pace throughout the remainder of the game but couldn't pull off a comeback win.
Jazz head coach Will Hardy mentioned that the team played hard but couldn't get it going offensively.
